artists into global stardom.\n\n==History==\n===2018\u20132019: Starting year and rise to stardom===\nBefore their debut, most of them trained for at least 2 years in ShowBT Philippines,. The company's goal was to produce talented individuals who have the passion and drive to make it in the industry. The group debuted on October 26, 2018, with their first single, \"Tilaluha\". They made their comeback on July 26, 2019, as they released a music video on [[YouTube]] for their second single, \"Go Up\".\n\nTheir main goal is to break into the music scene of the Philippines with their 'new and fresh sound'. The group has five members: Ken, Sejun, Stell, Josh, and Justin. They started to achieve mainstream popularity when a dance practice video of their second single \"Go Up\" went viral on Twitter last September 2, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|first=Rogin |last=Losa |url=https://www.scoutmag.ph/music/everyone-loves-the-boy-group-sb19-right-now-and-you-should-too-roginl-20190905 |title=Meet SB19, the P-pop group taking over the internet - Scout Magazine |publisher=Scoutmag.ph |date= 2019-09-05|accessdate=2019-09-10}}</ref>\n\n[[File:SB19 Official LOGO.jpg|thumb|The official SB19 logo]]\n\nOn November 14, 2019, the group won their first-ever local award as Favorite Group of the Year by the RAWR Awards 5th edition.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/en-ph/entertainment/celebrity/pinoy-group-sb19-enters-billboards-next-big-sound-chart/ar-BBX9ikB?li=BBr8Mkn |title=SB19 received Favorite Group of the Year award|accessdate=November 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe group unveiled its official fan base name, A'TIN (''pronounced as Eighteen''), on November 2, 2019. In a Facebook Live video, SB19 elaborated on the significance of the fandom name.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/features/20913/sb19-reveals-official-fandom-name |title=SB19 Reveals Official Fandom Name!|accessdate=November 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nSB19 made history on November 20, 2019, as the first Filipino group to land a spot on the [[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'s Next Big Sound Chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cnnphilippines.com/entertainment/2019/11/21/sb19-billboard-next-big-sound.html|title=Pinoy boyband SB19 makes it to Billboard's Next Big Sound|website=cnn|language=en|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref>  According to the Billboard report, the Next Big Sound chart measures \"the fastest growing artists over the past week across all major social music sites that are statistically expected to achieve future success.\" The chart is calculated by Next Big Sound, an American company that provides online music analysis.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rappler.com/entertainment/music/245469-sb19-lands-next-big-sound-chard-billboard|title=Pinoy group SB19 lands on Billboard's Next Big Sound chart|accessdate=November 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 25, SB19 signed contract under the label of [[Sony Music Philippines]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Push Team|url=https://push.abs-cbn.com/2019/12/25/fresh-scoops/look-sb19-signs-with-sony-music-222828 |title=SB19 signs with Sony Music|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2019\u20132020: Mainstream breakthrough===\nOn December 22, 2019, the group embarked on the first leg of their 10-city \"Get in the Zone\" free concert tour, starting with Negros Occidental and through 2020, on other major cities in the Philippines. Furthermore, it was announced on January 12, 2020 at [[ASAP (TV program)|ASAP Natin 'To]] that SB19 will be a regular guest for the month of January.\n\nThe group once again made history by being the first Filipino boy band to simultaneously chart on three [[Billboard charts|''Billboard'' charts]], placing 10th (peak @ 7th) on Social 50, 12th (peak @ 6th) on Next Big Sound, and 49th (peak @ 35th) on Emerging Artists for the week of March 7, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertainment.mb.com.ph/2020/03/05/sb19-charts-on-billboard-anew/|title=SB19 charts on Billboard anew|website=entertainment.mb.com.ph|access-date=March 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 9, 2020, SB19 was chosen as one of the emerging artists under [[Spotify]]'s RADAR Program.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/9330158/spotify-launches-global-artist-development-program-radar-alaina-castillo|title=Spotify Launches Global Emerging Artist Program RADAR With Alaina Castillo in the U.S.|website=billboard.com|access-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref>. The inaugural RADAR class features 36 performers from all over the world. Each will receive special incentives in their target markets, such as exposure of the playlist, documentary material and releases of \"Spotify Singles.\" They will also appear on the latest playlist On Our RADAR which seems ready for monthly refreshments<ref>{{cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2020/03/09/alaina-castillo-sb19-merci-mercy-more-confirmed-for-spotifys-radar-emerging-artists-program/|title=Alaina Castillo, SB19, Merci, Mercy, More Confirmed For Spotify\u2019s RADAR Emerging Artists Program|website=headlineplanet.com|access-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://newsroom.spotify.com/2020-03-09/36-new-artists-around-the-world-that-are-on-spotifys-radar/#SpotifyNews|title=36 New Artists Around the World That Are on Spotify\u2019s RADAR|website=newsroom.spotify.com/|access-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref>.\n\n==Impact==\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:SB19Official.png|thumb|right|PPop Sensation, [[SB19]]]] -->\nOn November 20, 2019, SB19 made history by being the first Filipino artist to chart and debut on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Next Big Sound chart debuting and peaking at #6. The Next Big Sound chart tracks \"the fastest accelerating artists during the past week, across all major social music sites, statistically predicted to achieve future success,\" according to the Billboard website.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/11/20/19/pinoy-group-sb19-enters-billboards-next-big-sound-chart|title=Pinoy group SB19 enters Billboard's Next Big Sound chart|website=news.abs-cbn.com|access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 3, 2019, the group broke the all-time record of longest stay at the No. 1 spot of [[Myx|Myx Daily Top Ten]] with Go Up reaching the top spot for 52 non-consecutive days.<ref>{{cite web|first=Twila |last=Bergania |url=https://www.cosmo.ph/entertainment/cosmoph-exclusive-interview-sb19-a968-20191229-lfrm3 |title=Exclusive: SB19 |publisher=Cosmo.ph |date= |accessdate=December 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nSB19 is also the most searched male personalities on Google Philippines in 2019. They also hold the record with Go Up for having the most weeks at #1 staying for 13 weeks at Pinoy MYX Countdown.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/headlines/2019/12/13/1976741/what-filipinos-searched-google-2019|title=What Filipinos searched in Google in 2019|website=philstar.com|access-date=December 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 24, 2019, SB19 again made history by being the first Filipino act to debut on Billboard Social 50 Chart landing on the 28th spot (peaked @ 7th)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kstreetmanila.com/2020/03/sb19-billboard-social-50-7th/#disqus_thread|title=SB19 Reaches New Peak At Billboard Rankings|publisher=KStreet Manila|date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>. Since then, SB19 is charting for seventeen weeks on the said chart. The ''Billboard Social 50'' is a popularity chart which ranks the most active musical artists on the world's leading social networking services.<ref name=\"Social 50\">{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com/charts/social-50 |title=Social 50 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=July 26, 2012}}</ref> Its data, published by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine and compiled by ''Next Big Sound'', is based collectively on each artist's weekly additions of friends, fans, and followers, along with artist website views and streaming mediums.\n\nOn January 9, 2020, at 7:00 pm, they released the music video for their third single \"Alab\" and immediately hit the top spot in Twitter world trends. Two days after, January 11, 2020, the music video reached 1 million views and hit its 2 million views after 9 days, January 20.\n\nOn March 26, 2020, for the second time, the group broke the all-time record of longest stay at the No. 1 spot of [[Myx|Myx Daily Top Ten]] with ''Alab (Burning)'' reaching the top spot for 53 (peaked @ 61) consecutive days<ref>{{cite web|url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/charts/myx-daily-top-10/03-25-2020|title=MYX Daily Top 10|publisher=[[MYX]]|date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>. The previous record was also their song ''Go up'' that stayed on top of the chart for 52 non-consecutive days<ref>{{cite web|url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/features/23077/sb19-alab-myx-daily-top-10-record|title=SB19'S \"ALAB\" SURPASSES MYX DAILY TOP 10 RECORD OF \"GO UP\"|publisher=[[MYX]]|date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>.\n\n==Members==\n*'''John Paulo Nase \"Sejun\" ''' ''(Leader, Main Rapper, Lead Vocalist, Dancer)'' was born in [[Cavite]] on September 14, 1994. Sejun is the main songwriter of the group.  He also likes hiphop and producing music. [[Demographics of South Korea|South Korea]]n rapper and singer-songwriter [[G-Dragon]] as his music inspiration. \n*'''Josh Cullen Santos \"Josh\" ''' ''(Lead Rapper, Dancer, Vocalist)'' was born in [[Pasig]] on October 22, 1993. He likes several rappers, such as [[Gloc-9]], [[Smugglaz]], Loonie, [[BTS]], and [[Big Bang (South Korean band)|Big Bang]]\u2019s G-Dragon.\n*'''Stellvester Ajero \"Stell\" ''' ''(Main Vocalist, Lead Dancer, Rapper)'' was born in [[Las Pi\u00f1as]] on June 16, 1995.\n*'''Felip Jhon Suson \"Ken\" ''' ''(Main Dancer, Vocalist, Rapper)'' was born in [[Cagayan de Oro|Cagayan De Oro]] on January 12, 1997.\n*'''Justin De dios \"Justin\"  ''' ''(Youngest, Visual, Vocalist, Dancer, Rapper)'' was born in [[Malabon]] on July 7, 1998.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://juanrepublic.ph/get-to-know-sb19-members-songs-profile/|title=SB19: Members, Songs and Discovery (Updated!)|last=ICA|date=2020-01-09|website=Juan Republic|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Singles===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n|+ List of singles, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width:300px;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Tilaluha\"\n|align=\"center\"|2018\n|rowspan=\"3\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Go Up\"\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\"|2019\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Alab (Burning)\"\n|}\n\n===Promotional single===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n|+ List of promotional single, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width:250px;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"'Wag Mong Ikunot ang Iyong Noo\"\n| align=\"center\"|2019\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Ikako\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/370911/sb19-to-release-new-song-ikako-amid-community-quarantine|title=SB19 to release new song \u2018ikako\u2019 amid community quarantine|last=Arcadio|first=Ryan|website=entertainment.inquirer.net|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\"|2020\n|-\n<!-- SB19 HAVEN'T OFFICIALLY RELEASED \"LOVE GOES\" (2018) AND \"HANGGANG SA HULI\" (2019) AS A SINGLE; EITHER COMMERCIAL OR PROMOTIONAL. AS OF 2020, BOTH SONGS ARE UNRELEASED -->\n|}\n\n===Chart performance===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n|+ List of other charted songs, with selected chart positions and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:13em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"3\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\" | Peak chart positions\n<!-- ITUNES (and DAILY TOP TEN) is a STATISTICAL PROJECTION that ends before the whole week and NOT AN OFFICIAL CHART\u2014same as MYX charts. But since there's NO OFFICIAL CHARTS FROM THE PHILIPPINES (e.g. Billboard Hot 100 PH *discontinued since 2017*) MYX CHARTS ARE THE MAJORITY OF RECOGNITION EVEN IF IT'S ONLY SHOWN IN TELEVISION.-->\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"3\" | Album\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | [[Philippines|PH]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:80%;\" | [[Myx#Programming|Hit Chart]]<br><ref name=\"Myx Hit 2019\">Peak chart positions in the Philippines:\n* For \"Go Up\": {{cite web|url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/charts/myx-hit-chart/10-13-2019|title=MYX Hit Chart|publisher=[[MYX]]|date=October 13, 2019}}\n* For \"Alab (Burning)\": {{cite web|url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/charts/myx-hit-chart/01-19-2020|title=MYX Hit Chart|publisher=[[MYX]]|date=January 19, 2020}}\n</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:80%;\" | [[Myx#Programming|Pinoy]]<br><ref>Peak chart positions in the Philippines:\n* For \"Go Up\": {{cite web|url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/charts/pinoy-myx-countdown/10-05-2019|title=Pinoy MYX Countdown|publisher=[[MYX]]|date=October 5, 2019}}\n* For \"Alab (Burning)\": {{cite web|url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/charts/pinoy-myx-countdown/01-18-2020|title=Pinoy MYX Countdown|publisher=[[MYX]]|date=January 18, 2020}}\n</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:80%;\" | [[Myx#Programming|Most Viewed]]<br><ref>Peak chart positions in the Philippines:\n* For \"Go Up\": {{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/HPMusicCharts2nd/posts/2570133643084827?__xts__[0]=68.ARC7XkpHif7eS2g65BYHNmHD9JvQ7nUCpoqGnn33-Tw34OlQogVjahA5TqG3KnVvdOpT_98f6Pv1bGA33lmeoNpYxORlOkvb1zVoJux6AWLqBmfYRusg_Fi_OcT4spFhXF_VakaG8yNuSbe407-QjOK9nWLg7aTEwDTTKP-5sfnd-esSW1keokUjaN51gZsd2DS-jAMCfjPILS5AoipVG5xRo0KNgdxzia173f8kd-Fv0n6REisG46ymjZWdCQ0m5r751aF6s4Xbvhb1MoAvF_o29S-TCn9vabBoPwuvlOXlfOBLmKvWW2C_zmz9EncPOfmf8fwPN3toyBah&__tn__=H-R|title=MYX Most Viewed|publisher=[[MYX]]|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}\n* For \"Alab (