]]<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20151127231351/http://sapnamagazine.com/2010/miss-pakistan-world-ayesha-gilani/</ref><ref>https://www.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/-i-was-born-ready</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.southasianoutlook.com/issues/2009/july/ayesha_gilani_miss_pakistan_world_2009.html|title=South Asian Outlook Ayesha Gilani Miss Pakistan World 2009|website=www.southasianoutlook.com}}</ref>  \n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| {{n/a|Unplaced in [[Miss Earth]] & Beauty of the World, Miss Tourism Queen International}}\n|-\n| 2008\n| [[Natasha Paracha]]<ref>https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/oops-pak-beauty-condones-blasts/cid/515859</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/12/19/nyregion/19bigcity.html|title=Pakistan May Not Be Ready for Its Beauty Queen|first=Susan|last=Dominus|date=18 December 2008|publisher=|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| {{n/a| Withdrew from [[Miss Earth]] and was replaced by Nosheen Idrees and did not compete in international pageants}}\n|-\n| 2007\n| [[Mahleej Sarkari]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20071215022448/http://www.indiaprwire.com/pressrelease/entertainment/200708073974.htm]</ref>\n| [[Balochistan (Pakistan)|Baluchistan]]\n| {{n/a| Miss Tourism Queen International}}\n|-\n| 2006\n| Sehr Mahmood<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/urdu/regional/story/2006/11/061123_beauty_contest_sq.shtml/|title=BBCUrdu.com|website=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n| [[Sindh (Pakistan)|Sindh]]\n| {{n/a|Unplaced in the [[Miss Earth]], Miss Elegant position won in Queen of the World}}\n|-\n| 2005\n| [[Naomi Zaman]]\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| {{n/a|Debut in [[Miss Earth]] & winner of Miss Dance Queen in Miss Tourism Queen International}}\n|-\n| 2004\n| Batool Cheema\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| {{n/a|Sent to Queen of the World 2009 and Miss Friendship 2009}}\n|-\n| 2003\n| [[Zehra Sheerazi]]\n| [[Sindh (Pakistan)|Sindh]]\n| [[Ottawa]]\n| {{n/a|Sent to World Miss University 2013}}\n|}\n\n===Representatives to Miss Earth===\nThe first representative to [[Miss Earth]] was [[Naomi Zaman]] in 2005 and since then there have been two years where Pakistan did not participate, 2007 & 2013. However, the winner of 2013 [[Shanzay Hayat]] represented Pakistan in the Miss Earth 2014 pageant held in Manila, Philippines on 29 November 2014. In 2008 [[Natasha Paracha]], Miss Pakistan World 2008 was replaced by runner up Nosheen Idrees.\n\n;Color keys\n{{plainlist|\n* {{color box|gold}} A year wherein the Pakistan earned a crown(s)\n* {{color box|#FFFF66}} A year wherein the Pakistan placed as a runner-up(s)\n* {{color box|#FFFACD}} A year wherein the Pakistan placed in the top 5, top 10, top 15, or as a semifinalist(s)\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Representative !! City, Province !! Ranking !! Special Awards\n|-\n| [[Miss Earth 2017|2017]]\n| [[Ramina Ashfaque]] \n| [[Sindh (Pakistan)|Sindh]]\n| Unplaced\n| Unplaced\n|-\n| [[Miss Earth 2016|2016]]\n| [[Anzhelika Tahir]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.samaa.tv/arts-culture/2016/10/pakistani-girl-from-sheikhupura-bags-gold-medal-in-miss-earth-2016/|title=Pakistani girl wins gold at beauty pageant - Samaa TV|website=www.samaa.tv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sunstar.com.ph/cagayan-de-oro/local-news/2016/10/19/ten-miss-earth-candidates-visit-iligan-ciy-504459|title=Ten Miss Earth candidates visit Iligan Ciy|first=Richel V.|last=Umel|date=19 October 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abplive.in/lifestyle/check-out-these-pakistani-beauty-queens-who-made-headlines-380467|title=Pakistani Beauty Qeens Who've Shed The Tag Of Being Conservative|first=ABP News|last=Bureau|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/world/2016/05/11/meet-anzhelika-tahir-pakistans-miss-world-2016|title=Meet Anzhelika Tahir, Pakistan's Miss World 2016|publisher=}}</ref>\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| Unplaced\n| {{gold01}} Talent Competition\n|-\n| [[Miss Earth 2014|2014]]\n| [[Shanzay Hayat]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beautypageantnews.com/shanzay-hayat-crowned-miss-pakistan-world-2013/|title=Shanzay Hayat Crowned Miss Pakistan World 2013 - Beauty Pageant News|date=1 September 2013|publisher=}}</ref>\n| [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]]\n| Unplaced\n| {{gold01}} Talent Competition\n|-\n| [[Miss Earth 2012|2012]]\n| [[Zanib Naveed]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ph.news.yahoo.com/video/bold-brave-answers-miss-pakistan-000000867.html|title=Bold and brave answers from Miss Pakistan Earth|publisher=}}</ref>\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| Unplaced\n| {{silver02}} Trivia Challenge<br> Award for press favorite <br>Miss SMDC\n|-\n| [[Miss Earth 2011|2011]]\n| [[Sanober Hussain]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/Hasleen-Kaur-at-Miss-Earth-2011/eventshow/11486607.cms|title=Hasleen Kaur with Miss Pakistan at Miss Earth in Manila, Philippines - BeautyPageants|website=Femina Miss India}}</ref>\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| Unplaced\n| Miss Friendship\n|-\n| [[Miss Earth 2009|2009]]\n| [[Ayesha Gilani]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashioncentral.pk/people-parties/events/festivals/story-350-miss-earth-pakistan-2009/|title=Miss Earth Pakistan 2009|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"missosology.org\">{{cite web|url=http://missosology.org/opinion/7077-focus-pakistans-participation-major-pageants/|title=IN FOCUS :: Pakistan's participation at major pageants - Missosology|last=Missosology|date=8 January 2014|publisher=}}</ref>\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| Unplaced\n| Top 15 Talent Finals\n|-\n| [[Miss Earth 2008|2008]]\n| Nosheen Idrees<ref name=\"missosology.org\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/130482/lifestyle/quake-worries-pakistan-s-miss-earth-candidate/|title=Quake worries Pakistan's Miss Earth candidate|website=GMA News Online}}</ref>\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| Unplaced\n| None\n|-\n| [[Miss Earth 2006|2006]]\n| Sehr Mahmood<ref name=\"missosology.org\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://southasianoutlook.com/issues/2007/june/celebrating_women_sehr_mahmood.html|title=South Asian Outlook - An Independent Monthly|first=Suresh Jaura, 33 Lafferty Street, Toronto, ONT M9C 5B5|last=CANADA|website=southasianoutlook.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theasiantoday.com/article.aspx?articleId=176 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-11-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129041140/http://www.theasiantoday.com/article.aspx?articleId=176 |archivedate=2014-11-29 }}</ref>\n| [[Sindh (Pakistan)|Sindh]]\n| Unplaced\n| None\n|-\n| [[Miss Earth 2005|2005]]\n| [[Naomi Zaman]]<ref name=\"missosology.org\"/>\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| Unplaced\n| None\n|}\n\n==Controversy==\n===2006===\nIn 2006, one of the runner ups of Miss Pakistan World was sent to China to represent Pakistan in Miss Bikini of the Universe. That caused a stir<ref>https://gulfnews.com/world/asia/pakistan/row-over-bikini-contestant-rages-1.255267</ref> in Pakistan.<ref>https://www.theasiantoday.com/index.php/2006/12/06/crowning-glory-for-miss-pakistan-beauty-pageants/</ref> However, Pakistan got its title of Best in Media<ref>https://www.houstonpress.com/news/bikini-revolution-6544639</ref> in the year 2006.<ref>http://old.paktribune.com/news/Pakistans-first-Miss-Bikini!-153100.html/?page=3</ref> The president of Miss Pakistan World, [[Sonia Ahmed]]<ref>https://www.financialexpress.com/archive/expat-pakistani-beauties-launch-bikini-rebellion/186675/</ref> defended the pageant and the titleholder<ref>https://www.dnaindia.com/world/report-a-rewarding-2006-for-pak-beauties-1065796</ref> and said that the contest will continue no matter what happened. \n\n===2008-2009===\nThe pageant has been criticised by Pakistani [[feminist]] [[Amna Buttar]] of the Asian-American Network Against Abuse of Human Rights, who wrote in an email to the ''[[New York Times]]'': <blockquote>\"In Pakistan, we are trying to get basic rights for women: right to marry, right to divorce, equal opportunity for job and education, and issues like Miss Pakistan create problems for this movement. An average Pakistani young woman does not want to wear a [[bikini]]<ref>https://gulfnews.com/news/asia/pakistan/row-over-bikini-contestant-rages-1.255267</ref> in public, and for her it is important to have equal opportunity and all focus should be on that, and not on a pageant where only the elite can participate.\"<ref name=\"NYT\"/></blockquote> [[Sonia Ahmed]] President of Miss Pakistan World defended<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.southasianpost.com/article/4747-beauty-aims-fight-beasts-pakistan.html|title=Beauty aims to fight the beasts of Pakistan {{!}} South Asian Post {{!}} Indo Canadian newspaper - Vancouver, Surrey, Calgary, Toronto, Brampton, Edmonton, Winnipeg, Montreal|website=www.southasianpost.com|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> the event as a movement to express one's rights and freedom to do as one wishes.\n\nIn 2008, Miss Pakistan World landed in yet another controversy<ref>http://www.rediff.com/news/2008/apr/16look.htm</ref> and that was pertaining to the President of Pakistan<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/I-want-to-date-Mush-the-hunk/articleshow/2957969.cms</ref>, [[Pervez Musharraf]].<ref>https://www.dnaindia.com/world/report-i-fell-in-love-with-musharraf-miss-pakistan-world-1160695</ref> The current Miss Pakistan World<ref>https://www.news18.com/news/india/musharraf-is-a-hunk-says-miss-pakistan-world-287413.html</ref> had expressed her desire<ref>http://www.sify.com/news/i-fell-in-love-with-musharraf-miss-pakistan-world-news-international-jegq0xbjjdgsi.html</ref> to date the President and confessed that she was in love<ref>https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/news/world/miss-pakistan-thinks-musharraf-is-a-hunk/articleshow/15802953.cms</ref> with the President.<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2008/12/19/nyregion/19bigcity.html</ref>\n\nIn December 2008, the reigning Miss Pakistan World, Natasha Paracha<ref>https://www.dawn.com/news/335008/</ref> used the word \"condone<ref>https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/oops-pak-beauty-condones-blasts/cid/515859</ref>\" instead of condemn<ref>https://southasia.typepad.com/south_asia_daily/2008/12/miss-pakistan-condones-mumbai-attacks-while-condemning-them-.html</ref> for the terrorist attacks on Mumbai. This caused the Indian community around the world to react.<ref>https://www.dnaindia.com/world/report-miss-pakistan-minces-her-words-condones-2611-1215341</ref>\n\n===2010===\nIn 2010 the pageant also fell into some controversy when it was held in the month of [[Ramadan]] as well as when the floods affected Pakistan 3 weeks prior to the event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bu.edu/today/node/11438|title=Beauty Pageant Rookie Wins Crown - BU Today - Boston University|publisher=|access-date=16 September 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100904033347/http://www.bu.edu/today/node/11438|archive-date=4 September 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Toronto Star\">[[Toronto Star]], [https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/850312--pakistani-beauty-pageant-to-go-ahead The flood in Pakistan will not stop the pageant in Toronto], Published On Thu 19 August 2010</ref><ref name=\"Globe and Mail\">Globe and Mail, ''[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/toronto/organizers-criticized-for-running-pakistani-pageant-in-wake-of-flood-disaster/article1679280/]'', Published on Thursday, 19 August 2010 10:30PM EDT</ref><ref name=\"The Guardian\">Alia Waheed, [[The Guardian]], \"[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/aug/19/pakistan-anger-beauty-contest-floods Miss Pakistan World pageant's timing causes dismay: Demands for Toronto beauty contest to be called off in light of humanitarian crisis brought by flooding in Pakistan]\", Thursday 19 August 2010 18.16 BST</ref>\n\n===2012===\nMost contestants<ref>http://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/news/article.cfm?c_id=6&objectid=10818312 New Zealand Herald</ref> who participated from around the world<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/14881538.Scottish_model_Madiha_Iqbal_to_compete_in_Miss_World_Pakistan_event_in_Canada/|title=Scottish model Madiha Iqbal to compete in Miss World Pakistan event in Canada|website=Asian Image}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/delhi-times/Miss-Pakistan-via-Canada/articleshow/1986409.cms|title=Miss Pakistan, via Canada - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref> were highlighted during the pageant<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theglobalindian.co.nz/miss-pakistan-world-2012/|title=New Zealander finalist at Miss Pakistan World title - The Global Indian|publisher=}}</ref> as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asianexpress.co.uk/2016/11/canadas-crown-aberdeen-beauty-queen-to-compete-in-miss-pakistan/|title=Canada's crown? Aberdeen beauty queen to compete in Miss Pakistan|publisher=}}</ref><ref>http://beauty.msn.co.nz/beautynews/latestnews/8496325/aucklander-up-for-miss-pakistan-crown Msn</ref> At a time when [[Pervez Musharraf]] was facing criticism from various political parties in Pakistan, one Miss Pakistan World confessed that she loved the president.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/world/report-i-fell-in-love-with-musharraf-miss-pakistan-world-1160695|title=I fell in love with Musharraf: Miss Pakistan World - Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|date=21 April 2008|publisher=}}</ref> \nDuring the Mumbai Attacks, Miss Pakistan World<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/world/report-pakistan-s-image-soiled-after-mumbai-attacks-beauty-queen-1214422|title=Pakistan's image soiled after Mumbai attacks: Beauty queen - Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|date=16 December 2008|publisher=}}</ref> winners spoke about the incident and gave statements regarding the India Pakistan tension. During a CNN interview, Miss Pakistan World [[Natasha Paracha]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/world/report-miss-pakistan-minces-her-words-condones-2611-1215341|title=Miss Pakistan minces her words, 'condones' 26/11 - Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|date=19 December 2008|publisher=}}</ref> used the word \"condone\" instead of \"condemn\" and it rolled on to become a huge controversy which dismayed many Indians.\n\n===2013-2019===\n\nIn 2016, [[Anzhelika Tahir]]<ref>https://www.parhlo.com/8-amazing-things-you-didnt-know-about-miss-pakistan-world-2016/</ref> was in the media<ref>https://www.parhlo.com/8-amazing-things-you-didnt-know-about-miss-pakistan-world-2016/</ref> in Pakistan for being criticized for representing [[Pakistan]] and there was discussions on how she is not Pakistani and should represent [[Ukraine]] only. In 2018<ref>https://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/miss-supranational/beauty-queens-from-india-and-pakistan-spread-the-message-of-peace/articleshow/66863581.cms</ref>, a photo of Miss India and Miss Pakistan World, [[Anzhelika Tahir]] went viral as both the beauty queens were holding their respective flags and calling out for peace between Pakistan and India. \n\nOn December 1, 2019<ref>https://nypost.com/2019/12/04/former-miss-pakistan-world-zanib-naveed-killed-in-car-crash/</ref> at 11:40 PM, former Miss Pakistan World 2012, [[Zanib Naveed]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thecanadianbazaar.com/migrating-to-Canada/zainab-naveed-miss-pakistan-world-2012/|title=Zainab Naveed Miss Pakistan World 2012|last=admin|date=2012-08-31|website=The Canadian Bazaar|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> died in a car crash accident. According to the police<ref>https://www.brecorder.com/2019/12/04/550282/former-miss-pakistan-world-zanib-naveed-dies-in-car-crash/</ref>, she attempted to take a curve to Route 1 and her vehicle struck a curb and flipped over. She<ref>https://en.dailypakistan.com.pk/04-Dec-2019/former-miss-pakistan-dies-in-car-crash-in-usa</ref> was ejected from the vehicle and died at the scene. Alcohol did not appear to be a factor in the crash, according to a preliminary investigation. Naveed<ref>https://dailyvoice.com/new-york/briarcliff/news/32-year-old-area-woman-killed-in-crash-was-miss-pakistan-world/780057/</ref> was the only person<ref>https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/public-safety/new-york-woman-killed-in-crash-along-icc-in-college-park-area/2019/12/02/1103c724-1518-11ea-8406-df3c54b3253e_story.html</ref> in the car.\n\nOn December 5th, 2019, [[Sonia Ahmed]]<ref>http://www.itssouthasian.com/former-miss-pakistan-world-zanib-naveed-dies-in-a-car-crash/</ref> President of Miss Pakistan World was interviewed by [[People (magazine)]]<ref>https://people.com/human-interest/former-miss-pakistan-world-zanib-naveed-dies-car-crash/</ref> Los Angeles USA for the untimely death of one of the winners of Miss Pakistan World [[Zanib Naveed]]. Ahmed answered, \u201cAs the President of Miss Pakistan World, we gave Naveed an amazing platform to represent Pakistan internationally and hearing about her death is very upsetting to all of us,\u201d Ahmed said. \u201cBeing a beauty queen to a country like Pakistan where there have been no beauty pageants on the soil of Pakistan is a tough job!\u201d \u201cNaveed along with other winners of Miss Pakistan World had a huge responsibility of carrying the title of a Muslim Nation,\u201d she continued. \u201cIt is a very upsetting time and terrible news and we can all hope and pray that her family gets through this painful situation.\u201d\n\n==Expansion==\n\nIn 2007 Mrs. Pakistan World,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ca.finance.yahoo.com/news/pakistan-gets-mrs-pakistan-world-221800650.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-02-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130412051958/http://ca.finance.yahoo.com/news/pakistan-gets-mrs-pakistan-world-221800650.html |archivedate=2013-04-12 }}</ref> for married women, was created as a spin-off. Both the Miss Pakistan World and the Mrs. Pakistan World pageant were created on the basis of issues faced by [[women in Pakistan]].The pageant is running successfully since 2007.\n\nIn 2011 Mr. Pakistan World, for single males of Pakistani descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barbiedressupgames.site/|title=Meet the new Mr. Pakistan World|website=pageantcenter.com}}</ref> The pageant has been running since 2011 and has been incorporated with the Miss Pakistan World pageant on stage.\n\nIn 2016, [[Sonia Ahmed]] got successful sending the first delegate directly from [[Pakistan]] to represent Pakistan in international pageants. Diya Ali<ref>https://tribune.com.pk/story/1648074/4-lahore-based-diya-ali-participate-miss-eco-international-2018/</ref> was the first representative from Pakistan<ref>https://images.dawn.com/news/1176877</ref> in 2016, and won the Miss Perpetual<ref>http://tribune.com.pk/story/1281667/pakistani-model-aiming-miss-world-title/</ref> title in [[Manila]], [[Philippines]] at the [[Miss Asia Pacific International]] pageant. That created a base for sending contestants directly from Pakistan for Miss Pakistan, Mrs. Pakistan and Mr. Pakistan, all new contests for Pakistan only.\n\n==See also==\n\n*[http://www.mrspakistanworld.com/ Mrs. Pakistan World] Official Site\n* [http://www.soniaahmedofficial.com/ Sonia Ahmed President] President of Mrs. Pakistan World\n* [http://www.misspakistanworld.com Miss Pakistan World] Miss Pakistan World\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.misspakistanworld.com/ Miss Pakistan World] website\n* ''[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-04-17/pakistan/27750143_1_pakistan-president-pervez-musharraf-hunk-pageants I want to date Mush the hunk]'', India Times article about one of the pageant's winners\n* ''[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Sania-bhabhi-must-stay-in-Pak/articleshow/5762816.cms Miss Pakistan 2009 comments on Sania & Shoaib Marriage]'', [[Times of India]]\n\n{{Miss Earth countries and territories}}\n\n[[Category:Pakistani awards]]\n[[Category:Women in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Miss Pakistan World winners|*]]\n[[Category:Beauty pageants in Canada]]\n[[Category:Beauty pageants for people of specific ethnic or national descents]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreliable sources|date=June 2016}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox organization\n|name         = Miss Pakistan World\n|image        =\n|image_border =\n|size         = \n|caption      = Logo of Miss Pakistan World\n|map          =\n|msize        =\n|mcaption     =\n|motto        = Celebrate the woman in you!\n|formation    = 2003\n|type         = [[Beauty Pageant]]\n|headquarters = [[Karachi]]\n|location     = [[Pakistan]]\n| membership =  [[Miss Earth]]\n|language     = [[English language|English]], [[Urdu]]\n|leader_title = President\n|leader_name  = [[Sonia Ahmed]] Since 2002. \n|website      = [http://www.misspakistanworld.com/ Miss Pakistan Official website]\n}}\n\n'''Miss Pakistan World''' is a [[beauty pageant]] for [[Pakistan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/When-Pakistani-beauty-queens-dazzled-in-bikini/eventshow/52688298.cms|title=When Pakistani beauty queens dazzled in bikini}}</ref> Till date it is the only original Pakistani beauty pageant that is internationally recognized in the world. The contestants of the Miss Pakistan World pageant are Pakistani girls who reside all over the world, as well as the participation is opened for Pakistani girls from Pakistan, as well as dual nationality holders. Miss Pakistan World has been running since 2002 and has expanded to launching Mrs. Pakistan World as well as Mr. Pakistan World.\n\n==History==\n\n===Founding Pakistan's Pageant Industry===\nFounded in 2002 by Pakistani-Canadian entrepreneur [[Sonia Ahmed]]<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/127030/miss-pakistan-world/|title=Miss Pakistan World|date=|work=The Express Tribune|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>, and in its first year called \"Miss Canada Pakistan<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gettyimages.ca/detail/news-photo/some-of-the-competitors-in-the-miss-canada-pakistan-contest-news-photo/165325588#some-of-the-competitors-in-the-miss-canada-pakistan-contest-in-the-picture-id165325588|title=AHMED (03/06/05) TORONTO, ONT Some of the competitors in the Miss Canada Pakistan contest in the foy|publisher=}}</ref>\", the contest is held in Canada because beauty pageants are highly [[Women in Islam|controversial]] in [[Pakistan]] and if it were held there, security for contestants would be too problematic.<ref name=\"NYT\">Dominus, Susan, \"[https://www.nytimes.com/2008/12/19/nyregion/19bigcity.html?_r=1&em Pakistan May Not Be Ready for Its Beauty Queen]\", ''[[New York Times]]'', 18 December 2008, retrieved 13 January 2009</ref> According to Ahmed, \"Pakistan's slow changing movement to liberate its women forbids<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.babushahi.com/opinion.php?oid=114|title=Bold & Beautiful|website=www.babushahi.com|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> such events from taking place on its soil.\"<ref name=\"MSN\">[[https://msn.com]], ''[http://lifestyle.in.msn.com/fashion/article.aspx?cp-documentid=1429533 Islamabad beauty is new Miss Pakistan World] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090227003822/http://lifestyle.in.msn.com/fashion/article.aspx?cp-documentid=1429533 |date=27 February 2009 }}'', 3 June 2008, retrieved 13 January 2009</ref> The name of the pageant was changed to Miss Pakistan World, when contestants from around the world started applying for the title. It is the only pageant existing for single Pakistani women in the world.{{cn|date=February 2018}} The first Miss Pakistan World to be crowned was [[Zehra Sheerazi]] on 1 February 2003 in [[Ottawa|Ottawa, Ontario]], Canada. Sheerazi went on to represent Pakistan in Pakistan's first ever debut in international pageants, [[World Miss University]]. The winners<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masala.com/islamabad-beauty-is-new-miss-pakistan-world-3492.html|title=Islamabad beauty is new Miss Pakistan World|publisher=}}</ref> went on to represent Pakistan in international pageants as well as the contestants came from diverse backgrounds to participate.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/karin-kloosterman/meet-miss-green-pakistan-_b_1023454.html|title=Meet Miss \"Green\" Pakistan World|first=Karin|last=Kloosterman|date=21 October 2011|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n===Mrs. Pakistan World & Mr. Pakistan World===\nIn 2007, Ahmed went on to create Mrs. Pakistan World and in 2011 Mr. Pakistan World all male model competition was launched. Mr. Pakistan World and Miss Pakistan World take place together on stage and both winners are announced together.{{citation needed|date=November 2016}}\n\n===USA Based===\nIn 2014, [[Sonia Ahmed]], President of Miss Pakistan World, shifted the entire pageant and its team to base itself in [[New Jersey]], US for the year 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.my9nj.com/story/26474107/2014-miss-pakistan-world-pageant-coming-to-edison |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-10-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010080437/http://www.my9nj.com/story/26474107/2014-miss-pakistan-world-pageant-coming-to-edison |archivedate=2014-10-10 }}</ref> This was the first time the pageant was held out<ref name=\"myfoxtampabay.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.myfoxtampabay.com/story/26474107/2014-miss-pakistan-world-pageant-coming-to-edison|title=Tampa Bay news, weather forecast, radar, and sports from WTVT-TV - FOX 13 News - FOX 13 Tampa Bay|last=FOX|website=FOX13news}}</ref> of its home base in Canada. This not only attracted new local contestants from the US<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thealternativepress.com/articles/2014-miss-pakistan-world-pageant-coming-to-edison|title=2014 Miss Pakistan World Pageant Coming to Edison|publisher=}}</ref> but also got more contestants attracted from different parts of the world. In 2015 & 2016 the pageant was back in Toronto,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nation.com.pk/entertainment/28-Aug-2012/new-yorker-wins-miss-pakistan-world-pageant|title=New Yorker wins Miss Pakistan world pageant|publisher=}}</ref> Canada.\n\n==Titleholders==\nDespite being called \"Miss Pakistan World\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newseastwest.com/miss-pakistan-contestants-sizzle/|title=Miss Pakistan contestants sizzle|website=newseastwest.com}}</ref> the pageant sends its delegates to the [[Miss Earth]]. [[Zehra Sheerazi]] was the first Miss Pakistan World to enter into an international beauty pageant, World Miss University 2003 in Korea. The first girl of mixed race, [[Anzhelika Tahir]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parhlo.com/miss-pakistan-world-has-landed-her-first-pakistani-film-alongside-some-big-names-and-we-are-really-excited/|title=Miss Pakistan World Has Landed Her First Pakistani Film Alongside Some Big Names And We Are Really Excited!|date=12 September 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jehanpakistan.com/epaper/detail_news.php?news=/epaper/epaper/karachi/220216/p10-020.jpg#sthash.kVk91dzB.omVeEjUk.dpbs|title=JehanPakistan ePaper - \u062c\u06c1\u0627\u06ba \u067e\u0627\u06a9\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631|website=www.jehanpakistan.com}}</ref> was crowned Miss Pakistan World on 31 October 2015. The pageant also sends its runners-up to various international pageants around the world: Miss Tourism Queen International, Miss Earth, World Miss University, Miss Supertalent, Miss Eco International, Bikini of the Universe, Beauty of the World and many others.\n\n;Color keys\n{{plainlist|\n* {{color box|gold}} A year wherein the Pakistan earned a crown(s)\n* {{color box|#FFFF66}} A year wherein the Pakistan placed as a runner-up(s)\n* {{color box|#FFFACD}} A year wherein the Pakistan placed in the top 5, top 10, top 15, or as a semifinalist(s)\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Representative\n! Province\n! Host City\n! Host Country\n! Placement at International Pageants\n|-\n| 2020\n| \n| TBA\n| [[Toronto]]\n|| {{flag|Canada}}\n| TBA\n|-\n| 2019\n| Arooj Bokhari\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| [[Toronto]]\n|| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{n/a|sent to [[Miss Tourism International]] 2019 [[World Miss University]] 2019}}\n|--\n| 2017/2018\n| [[Diya Ali]]<ref>https://tribune.com.pk/story/1428821/pakistani-model-diya-ali-inching-closer-miss-world-dream/</ref><ref>https://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/miss-world/i-admire-aishwarya-rai-for-her-beauty/articleshow/64061358.cms</ref>\n| [[Sindh (Pakistan)|sindh]]\n| [[Toronto]]\n|| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{n/a|Sent to Miss Eco International<ref>https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/651884-mahleej-sarkari-wins-miss-pakistan-world-2007/</ref> \n|-\n| 2016/2017\n| Ramina Ashfaque\n| [[Sindh]]\n| [[Toronto]]\n| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{n/a|sent to [[Miss Earth 2017]]}}\n|- \n| 2015 \n| [[Anzhelika Tahir]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://newseastwest.com/miss-pakistan-2015-anzhelika-tahir/|title=Miss Pakistan 2015 Anzhelika Tahir|website=newseastwest.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.com.pk/epaper/Index.aspx?Issue=NP_LHE&Page=Magazine_Page015&Date=20160202&Pageno=15|title=Daily Express Urdu Newspaper - Latest Pakistan News - Breaking News|website=www.express.com.pk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jehanpakistan.com/epaper/detail_news.php?news=/epaper/epaper/karachi/190416/p10-029.jpg#sthash.X1YTZA35.XuXL9JW8.dpbs|title=JehanPakistan ePaper - \u062c\u06c1\u0627\u06ba \u067e\u0627\u06a9\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631|website=www.jehanpakistan.com}}</ref>\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| [[Toronto]]\n| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{n/a|Sent to [[Miss Earth]] [[World Miss University]], World Super Model 2016, Miss Eco International<ref>https://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/others/anzhelika-tahir-to-represent-pakistan-at-miss-eco-international/articleshow/58024992.cms</ref>, Miss Supertalent 2016 & Miss Supranational 2018<ref>https://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/miss-supranational/anzhelika-tahir-crowned-miss-supranational-pakistan-2018/articleshow/66652861.cms</re